body: Yes, `OrderedDict` is a dictionary that supports `pop_item`. I can't really type it as a `TypedDict` because of the extra `popitem` method, and mypy doesn't have an `OrderedTypedDict` at the moment. I could try subclassing TypedDict though and see if that gets anywhere... or refactor the code so that we don't need an OrderedDict anymore
